description:
This course is Harvard University's introduction to programming using a language called R, a popular language for statistical computing and graphics in data science and other domains. This  By course’s end, learn to package, test, and share R code for others to use.

💻 Slides, source code, and more at https://cs50.harvard.edu/r/

✏️ Carter Zenke teaches this course.

❤️ Support for this channel comes from our friends at Scrimba – the coding platform that's reinvented interactive learning: https://scrimba.com/freecodecamp

⭐️ Contents ⭐️
- 0:00:00 Introduction
- 0:02:27 Representing Data
- 1:41:48 Transforming Data
- 3:20:12 Applying Functions
- 4:31:51 Tidying Data
- 5:44:04 Visualizing Data
- 6:59:35 Testing Programs
- 7:57:02 Packaging Programs
